  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best books for the self preparation of EE GATE?",
  "response": "Preparing for the GATE (Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering) in Electrical Engineering (EE) requires a thorough understanding of the syllabus, practice with diverse problems, and familiarity with the exam pattern. Here are some of the best books recommended for self-preparation for EE GATE:\n\n### 1. **General Aptitude**\n- **Verbal Ability and Reading Comprehension**:\n  - **\"A Modern Approach to Verbal & Non-Verbal Reasoning\"** by R.S. Aggarwal\n\n- **Numerical Ability**:\n  - **\"Quantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations\"** by R.S. Aggarwal\n  - **\"Fast Track Objective Arithmetic\"** by Rajesh Verma\n\n### 2. **Engineering Mathematics**\n- **\"Higher Engineering Mathematics\"** by B.S. Grewal\n- **\"Advanced Engineering Mathematics\"** by Erwin Kreyszig\n\n### 3. **Core Electrical Engineering Subjects**\n#### Electric Circuits:\n- **\"Engineering Circuit Analysis\"** by William H. Hayt, Jack E. Kemmerly, and Steven M. Durbin\n- **\"Fundamentals of Electric Circuits\"** by Charles K. Alexander and Matthew N.O. Sadiku\n\n#### Electromagnetic Fields:\n- **\"Elements of Electromagnetics\"** by Matthew N.O. Sadiku\n- **\"Engineering Electromagnetics\"** by William H. Hayt and John A. Buck\n\n#### Signals and Systems:\n- **\"Signals and Systems\"** by Alan V. Oppenheim, Alan S. Willsky, and S. Hamid Nawab\n- **\"Signals and Systems\"** by Simon Haykin and Barry Van Veen\n\n#### Electrical Machines:\n- **\"Electrical Machinery Fundamentals\"** by Stephen J. Chapman\n- **\"Electric Machines\"** by D.P. Kothari and I.J. Nagrath\n\n#### Power Systems:\n- **\"Power System Analysis\"** by John J. Grainger and William D. Stevenson\n- **\"Power System Engineering\"** by D.P. Kothari and I.J. Nagrath\n\n#### Control Systems:\n- **\"Modern Control Engineering\"** by Katsuhiko Ogata\n- **\"Control Systems Engineering\"** by Norman S. Nise\n\n#### Electrical and Electronic Measurements:\n- **\"Electrical and Electronic Measurements and Instrumentation\"** by R.K. Rajput\n- **\"Electronic Instrumentation\"** by H.S. Kalsi\n\n#### Analog and Digital Electronics:\n- **\"Microelectronics Circuits\"** by Adel S. Sedra and Kenneth C. Smith\n- **\"Digital Design\"** by Morris Mano and Michael D. Ciletti\n\n### 4. **Practice and Previous Year Papers**\n- **\"GATE Guide Electrical Engineering\"** by GKP\n- **\"GATE Electrical Engineering\"** by Made Easy Publications\n- **Previous Years\u2019 Solved Papers by GATE Forum** or **ACE Engineering Academy**\n\n### 5. **Online Resources and Mock Tests**\n- **NPTEL** (Online Courses by IIT Professors)\n- **Made Easy, Testbook, and Unacademy** (Provide online courses, mock tests, and study materials)\n- **GATE Score App** (For practice questions and mock tests)\n\n### Study Plan Tips:\n1. **Understand the Syllabus**: Break down the syllabus into manageable sections and plan your study schedule accordingly.\n2. **Conceptual Clarity**: Focus on understanding the fundamental concepts before diving into problem-solving.\n3. **Practice Regularly**: Solve as many problems as possible from different sources to get a grip on various types of questions.\n4. **Mock Tests**: Regularly take mock tests to assess your preparation and improve time management skills.\n5. **Revise**: Keep revising important topics and formulas regularly to retain them.\n\nGood luck with your GATE preparation!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
